          "text": "Based on my exploration of the agent-tui codebase, I can provide you with a **feasibility analysis** for adding a web interface.\n\n---\n\n## Feasibility Score: **9/10** ✅\n\nThe project architecture makes this **highly feasible**. Here's why:\n\n### Why This Is Straightforward\n\n1. **Clean Protocol Abstraction**: The existing `AgentProtocol` interface (`stream`, `approve_tool`, `answer_question`, `cancel`, etc.) can be reused exactly as-is. Both `StubAgent` and `DeepAgentsAdapter` will work without modification.\n\n2. **Event-Driven Architecture**: The `AgentEvent` / `EventType` system already models everything needed for a web interface:\n   - `MESSAGE_CHUNK` → Server-Sent Events for streaming responses\n   - `TOOL_CALL` → WebSocket notifications requiring approval\n   - `ASK_USER` → Modal/prompt in the browser\n   - `STATUS_UPDATE`, `TOKEN_UPDATE` → UI state updates\n\n3. **Adapter Pattern**: The `AgentAdapter` class shows exactly how to dispatch events to a UI. You'd create a web equivalent that dispatches to WebSocket/HTMX endpoints instead of TUI widgets.\n\n4. **No Business Logic Coupling**: Sessions, file operations, tool handling, and DeepAgents integration are all in the service layer — no terminal-specific code blocks reuse.\n\n### Stack Compatibility Assessment\n\n| Component | Fit | Notes |\n|-----------|-----|-------|\n| **FastAPI** | ✅ Excellent | Native WebSocket and SSE support, async-first |\n| **Jinja2** | ✅ Excellent | Can reuse rendering logic for tool displays |\n| **Tailwind CSS** | ✅ Excellent | Perfect for the complex UI (diffs, code blocks, tool results) |\n| **HTMX** | ✅ Excellent | Ideal for message streaming (`hx-sse`), tool approval modals |\n| **Alpine.js** | ✅ Good | Manages local UI state (theme, sidebar toggle, input focus) |\n\n### Key Implementation Points\n\n1. **WebSocket + SSE Hybrid**: Use WebSockets for bidirectional communication (sending messages, approvals) and SSE for streaming agent responses (simpler